<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
  <!--
    Entitlements for the ad-hoc-signed Skima bundle. The Node sidecar
    (skima-server) embeds V8, which requires JIT-able executable memory
    pages. macOS Hardened Runtime (which Tauri's bundler enables by
    default on ad-hoc signed builds since Tauri v2) blocks JIT unless
    we opt back into it here. Without these entitlements the sidecar
    aborts at v8::Isolate::Initialize on launch, taking demo-data load
    and the setup wizard down with it.

    Required for V8:
      - allow-jit: re-enable mmap PROT_EXEC for the JIT code cache
      - allow-unsigned-executable-memory: V8 writes to its JIT pages
        after marking them executable, which Hardened Runtime forbids
        by default

    Useful for the wider Node ecosystem the sidecar pulls in:
      - disable-library-validation: lets Node load native .node addons
        (Prisma's query engine, bcrypt, sqlite3) that are not signed
        by Apple and may have different team identifiers
      - disable-executable-page-protection: more permissive page
        permissions for older V8 builds; harmless if unused
  -->
  <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit</key>
  <true/>
  <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory</key>
  <true/>
  <key>com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation</key>
  <true/>
  <key>com.apple.security.cs.disable-executable-page-protection</key>
  <true/>
</dict>
</plist>
